channel.title: Help? Adding on mopar toplist
channel.description:
Hello,
I have a server hosted on my VPS and it's client is connecting to it just fine. I can't seem to get it to go on the toplist though, it's saying it's offline.
My only thing I'd say is wrong is the port, but How would I check what port I should be using?
It's a 317
Thanks

item.title: Help? Adding on mopar toplist
item.dc:creator: @GaMuPk GaMuPk
item.description:
@GaMuPk wrote:

43594, typical port and what I had expected. However that doesn’t seem to be the issue as it’s still saying it is offline.

Any suggestions? It’s gamupk.no-ip.org port 43594, guarantee you it’s online however the sever toplist(as well as rune-server’s top list) is saying it’s offline, which is very odd.

If you can help, that’d be great

Brandon
